  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study was to to evaluate the effect of sarpogrelate, a selective serotonin
      receptor antagonist, and high dose statin on the reduction of coronary spasm in the patients
      with variant angina.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
