  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Clinical history of chest pain compatible with variant angina; morning chest pain
             aggravated by cold exposure.

          -  Angiographically proven coronary spasm; TIMI flow &lt; 3 by spontaneous coronary spasm or
             intracoronary ergonovine spasm provocation test.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Cardiac arrest by coronary spasm

          -  Left main coronary spasm

          -  Significant fixed coronary artery stenosis; Diameter stenosis &gt; 70% in the major
             epicardial artery by coronary angiography

          -  Left ventricular ejection fraction &lt; 30%

          -  Coagulation disorders or bleeding tendency (Platelet count &lt; 50k, PT INR &gt; 2.0)

          -  Significant liver disease (AST or ALT &gt; 100 U/ml)

          -  Renal failure (S-Cr &gt; 2.0 mg/dl)

          -  hypersensitivity for statin

          -  Pregnancy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
